included.description: Treasure Trip is a task organizer for children, who complete tasks displayed on a physical board in the house with the promise of a possible reward. Treasure Trip features a colorful display with swappable style templates, enabling families to customize the board to their liking. As children progress along the road map, the board becomes increasingly lit up, making it an attractive and fun fixture to have. Additionally, with a variety of rule settings, Treasure Trip aims to not only reward children for hard work, but motivate them to be more proactive in adopting positive behaviors and learning important lessons along the way.

included.description:
The Michigan Association of Computer Users in Learning (MACUL) is an organization that provides tools and organizes conferences to promote the use of technology in education in the state of Michigan. The purpose of this project was to identify how MACUL can improve their internal communications structure to increase efficiency while mitigating external breakdowns.

Through the use of Contextual Inquiry methods such as interviews and observations, we identified problems and issues that the MACUL staff members were experiencing. Major findings include the effectiveness of their office structure due to the length of time staff members have been working together, as well as the upcoming retirement of the Executive Director which highlights how changes need to be made to allow for this and any future transitions to be executed smoothly. Specifically what we have done include:

1. Examined the information flow of communication processes among staff through contextual inquires
2. Constructed an affinity wall and created consolidated models to examine possible communication problems 
3. Provided suggestions for better information sharing internally among staff
included.title: Internal Communication Flow Analysis for MACUL
